<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> The consolidation into a single-party regime took place during the first three and a half years after the revolution, which included the period of <a href="/wiki/War_Communism" title="War Communism" class="mw-redirect">War Communism</a> and an election in which multiple parties competed. See Leonard Schapiro, <i>The Origin of the Communist Autocracy: Political Opposition in the Soviet State, First Phase 1917–1922.</i> Cambridge, MA: Harvard University Press, 1955, 1966.</li>
